    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That makes sense. When you say the high-density area has \"volatile market trends\" because of the shifting demographics, do you think those demographic changes themselves actually drive the risk? Like, if the neighborhood becomes more diverse/multi-cultural, does that typically correlate with lower property value stability compared to a more homogenous, established area?",
